# Calendly slug shared by the booking embeds: the homepage "Get started" section
# (15-minute discovery call) and the /advisory page's PAID introductory call with
# Rengan ($150, charged at booking via Stripe inside Calendly).
# Format: "username/event-slug" taken from the live Calendly URL
# (calendly.com/<username>/<event-slug>).
# Leave the placeholder and the embeds show a graceful "booking opens shortly"
# notice; set the real slug once the Calendly event is live.
NEXT_PUBLIC_CALENDLY_LINK=REPLACE-WITH-RENGAN-EVENT
NEXT_PUBLIC_CALENDLY_DISCOVERY_CALL=REPLACE-WITH-DISCOVERY-EVENT-LINK

# YouTube Data API v3 key — powers the podcast video sections (advisory calendar
# + team page). Server-only (no NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix), so it is never exposed to
# the browser. The channel id/url live in content/global.json → youtube. Until
# this and the channel id are set, the video sections stay hidden.
# Create at https://console.cloud.google.com → APIs & Services → Credentials →
# Create API key, after enabling "YouTube Data API v3". Restrict it to that API.
YOUTUBE_API_KEY=REPLACE-WITH-YOUTUBE-DATA-API-KEY
